OL,6,FThe current DUP leader was a senior
OL,7,Fmember of the Ulster Unionists'
OL,8,Fnegotiating delegation in 1998 when
OL,9,Fthe Good Friday Agreement was struck.
OL,10,FHours before the historic accord was
OL,11,Fagreed, the Lagan Valley MP famously
OL,12,Fleft Castle Buildings at Stormont in
OL,13,Fprotest at what his party was about to
OL,14,Fsign up to.JHe eventually left the
OL,15,Fparty and joined the DUP in 2003.JHe
OL,16,Fadded: "When you are in leadership,
OL,17,Fsometimes that can be a lonely place.
OL,18,FWhen you are in leadership you've got
OL,19,Fto step out and step up.J"You have got
